That can't be: fully vaccinated must be subset of at least one dose, so fully vaccinated % cannot exceed at least one dose. That's an inconsistency, suggests either misreading or data error. Could be the description reversed values, but the analysis says fully vaccinated 43% > 36% at least one dose, which is impossible. That is a potential "Incorrect reading of chart" error, or "Cherry-picking" maybe, but mainly it's an incorrect reading/inconsistent data. Could be a mistake by LLM, not necessarily visualization. Actually fully higher), 36% vs 43% (gap -7% but reversed), 50-55% vs 48-50% (gap small). So they think gap consistent but not exactly.

Thus likely misleading aspect is "Incorrect reading of chart". Also maybe "Cherry-picking"? Not really.
